From Subject Re dogs In article MS Ikkoku mrc Ikkoku Mark Crispin writes With a hostile dog or one which you repeatedly encounter stronger measures may be This is the face First and there is very important make sure you NEVER face off a dog on his Face him off on the road not on his If necessary have a large stick rolled up newspaper something the beast will understand is something that will hurt him Stand your ground then slowly Your mental attitude is that you are VERY ANGRY and are going to dispense TERRIBLE The larger the dog the greater your This tactic depends for its effectiveness on the dog's conformance to a psychological norm that may not actually apply to a particular I've tried it with some success before but it won't work on a Charlie Manson dog or one that's really really A large Irish Setter taught me this in my yard apparently HIS territory one I'm sure he was playing a game with The game was probably Kill the VERY ANGRY Neighbor Before He Can Dispense the TERRIBLE Chuck Rogers